description.narrative:
The aim of Darfur Community Peace and Stability Fund (DCPSF) is to improve security and stabilization of communities affected by conflict through utilization of effective conflict management mechanisms, peace dividends and support to peace infrastructures and durable solutions that augment peaceful coexistance and social cohesion. 
The DCPSF has four expected outputs:
1) Community-based conflict resolution and reconciliation mechanisms are in use and working effectively to resolve conflict;
2) Peace dividends for community interdependence and co-existance are delivered;
3) Women's organisations, including those representing pastoralists women, empowered to meaningfully participate in local and state-level peacebuilding platforms;
4) Improved networking, coordination and learning between local and state-level peacebuilding institutions.
